# web-auto ‚Äî project knowledge base

Repo: `rikinptl/web-auto`. Automated B2B pipeline: scrape Google Maps businesses **without websites** ‚Üí track in Google Sheets ‚Üí DeepSeek generates copy ‚Üí Jinja2 renders static site ‚Üí deploy to GitHub Pages.

## Branches

| Branch | Purpose | Deploy target |
|--------|---------|---------------|
| **`main`** | Lead pipeline (scraper, site generator, CI). Source of truth for automation. | **kem-llc org repos** ‚Äî one public repo per lead via `scripts/deploy_org_site.py` ‚Üí `https://kem-llc.github.io/{slug}/` |
| **`monitor`** | Founder dashboard UI (`monitor/`). Same pipeline code + Next.js monitor app. | **Vercel** ‚Äî set Root Directory to `monitor`, branch to `monitor` |

Do not mix deploy configs: Pages = `main` + `site/` artifact; Vercel = `monitor` branch + `monitor/` folder.

## `main` ‚Äî pipeline layout

```
scrap.py                 # Playwright scraper; writes leads, syncs Sheet
scripts/
  resolve_search.py      # niche+city ‚Üí SEARCH_QUERY (from config/markets.json)
  sheets.py              # Google Sheets CRUD; HEADERS below
  generate_site.py       # DeepSeek ‚Üí site/site-data.json
  render_site.py         # Jinja2 templates ‚Üí site/*.html
  deploy_org_site.py   # Create kem-llc/{slug} repo, push site/, enable Pages
  setup_kem_llc.py     # Verify org + set ORG_DEPLOY_TOKEN / DEPLOY_ORG on repo
config/markets.json      # 20 niches √ó 15 cities (DFW phase 1)
templates/               # Jinja2 site templates
site/                    # Generated static output (deployed to Pages)
data/leads.json          # Scraped leads array (empty in repo; populated by CI)
.github/workflows/deploy.yml  # workflow_dispatch ONLY (no push trigger)
```

### Pipeline flow (GitHub Actions)

1. Manual dispatch: pick **niche**, **city**, **max_results**
2. `scrap.py` ‚Äî scroll Maps in batches, fast website check, full extract only for no-website leads; stops when `MAX_RESULTS` qualified or `MAX_CHECK_LISTINGS` checked
3. `replace_inventory()` on scrape ‚Äî **reads sheet first**, skips known businesses, **upserts** only new leads (does not wipe sheet)
4. `generate_site.py` ‚Äî DeepSeek copy per lead (parallel matrix jobs)
5. `deploy_org_site.py` ‚Äî one `kem-llc/{slug}` repo per lead (parallel, up to 5 at once)
6. `update_sheet.py` ‚Äî writes each lead's `live_url` + copy Done

### Google Sheet columns

Business Name | Niche | Phone | City | Scraped Status | DeepSeek Copy Status | Live URL | Google Maps URL

### Lead JSON fields

`name`, `niche`, `category`, `phone`, `address`, `city`, `rating`, `reviews`, `website` (always null), `google_maps_url`, `scraped_status`, `copy_status`, `live_url`

Mock data (Joe's Plumbing) is blocked. `data/leads.json` in repo should stay `[]`.

### CI secrets & vars

- Secrets: `DEEPSEEK_API_KEY`, `GOOGLE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON`, `ORG_DEPLOY_TOKEN` (PAT with kem-llc repo create)
- Vars: `GOOGLE_SHEETS_SPREADSHEET_ID`, `DEPLOY_ORG` (`kem-llc`)
- Scraper env: `REQUIRE_LEADS=true`, `MAX_CHECK_LISTINGS=100`, `HEADLESS=true`

### Scraper notes

- Uses direct `/maps/place/` URLs (not sidebar clicks) ‚Äî reliable in headless CI
- Never use `networkidle` on Google Maps
- Niche+city combos like plumber+Dallas may yield zero no-website leads (most have sites) ‚Äî pipeline correctly fails with `REQUIRE_LEADS`

## `monitor` ‚Äî founder dashboard

Next.js 15 app in `monitor/`. Aggregates Sheet + GitHub Actions API into one UI.

```
monitor/src/
  app/api/dashboard/   # Aggregated JSON for UI
  app/api/auth/        # Optional MONITOR_PASSWORD cookie auth
  components/          # Stats, funnel, leads table, runs, market grid
  lib/sheets.ts        # Read-only Google Sheets
  lib/github.ts        # Workflow run history (deploy.yml)
  lib/dashboard.ts     # Stats + coverage computation
```

### Vercel env (see `monitor/.env.example`)

`GOOGLE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON`, `GOOGLE_SHEETS_SPREADSHEET_ID`, `GITHUB_TOKEN`, `GITHUB_REPO`, `MONITOR_PASSWORD` (recommended), link URLs optional.

## Local dev

- Python 3.12 + `pip install -r requirements.txt` + Playwright chromium
- Copy `.env.example` ‚Üí `.env` with service account path + API keys
- Monitor: `cd monitor && npm install && npm run dev`

